DRESSOR PLAINS SOLAR, LLC
RATE SCHEDULE FERC NO. 1
Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service
Dressor Plains Solar, LLC ("Dressor Plains") provides Reactive Supply and Voltage Control from Generation Sources Service ("Reactive Supply Service") from the Dressor Plains generating facility ("Dressor Plains Facility").
Dressor Plains is a solar generating facility located in Fayette County, Illinois. The Dressor Plains Facility is interconnected to transmission facilities owned by Ameren Illinois Company and under the operational control of the Midcontinent Independent System Operator, Inc. ("MISO").
This Rate Schedule FERC No. 1 sets forth Dressor Plains' revenue requirement for Reactive Supply Service from the Dressor Plains Facility. This Rate Schedule shall be effective upon the date authorized by the Federal Energy Regulatory Commission.
Dressor Plains' monthly fixed revenue requirement consists of the charge for the Fixed Capability Component. Payment to Dressor Plains shall be subject to Schedule 2 of MISO's Open Access Transmission Tariff.
MONTHLY REVENUE REQUIREMENT:
The Annual Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $500,000.00. The Monthly Reactive Service Revenue Requirement is: $41,666.67.
